// docs/spec/en/05-unions-and-packed-layout.md §9.4(5) and its note: "If
// the array-bound constant-expression is not a constant expression, the
// program is ill-formed ... This document does not thereby introduce
// variable-length arrays: ... an array-bound constant-expression that is
// not a constant expression remains ill-formed in SCPP26, exactly as in
// strict ISO C++." A non-`const`, non-`constexpr` local variable is not
// usable in a constant expression, so it must be rejected with a clean
// diagnostic -- not silently accepted as a VLA now that the parser
// accepts arbitrary expressions in this position.
int main() {
    int n = 5;
    char runtime_bound[n];
    runtime_bound[0] = 'a';
    return 0;
}
